### 3. Base `SpannerSqlAstTranslator.visitUpdateStatementOnly` (lines 155-166)

**File:** `hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/dialect/sql/ast/SpannerSqlAstTranslator.java`

```java
@Override
protected void visitUpdateStatementOnly(UpdateStatement statement) {
    // Spanner requires a WHERE in update clause so we add "where true" if there is none
    if ( !hasWhere( statement.getRestriction() ) ) {
        renderUpdateClause( statement );
        renderSetClause( statement.getAssignments() );
        appendSql( " where true" );
        visitReturningColumns( statement.getReturningColumns() );
    }
    else {
        super.visitUpdateStatementOnly( statement );
    }
}
```

This handles HQL/AST-level UPDATE statements. If there's no WHERE clause, it manually adds `where true` because Spanner requires a WHERE clause. Otherwise, it delegates to the superclass.

